            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>ŠMY son of [PN]</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The name Shammai was borne by three men from the tribe of Judah (1 Chron. 2:28),
                    is attested as an element in a number of Semitic names and occurs in a second
                    century BCE inscription from Mount Gerizim. The sign after the bet could also be
                    read as a numeral – the Phoenician number ten: the text would then read "ŠMY, in
                    (the year) 10" or "ŠMY, on the tenth [of month X]".</p>
            </div>
